  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.cyc.kb.Context, com.cyc.kb.KbIndividual, com.cyc.kb.KbObject, com.cyc.kb.KbObject.KbObjectWithArity, com.cyc.kb.KbTerm

    public class ContextImpl
extends KbIndividualImpl<ElMt>
implements com.cyc.kb.Context
    A Context object is a facade for a #$Microtheory in Cyc KB. A context is a grouping of assertions that share a set of common assumptions. Each Assertion has to be explicitly stated to be true in at least one context.

      • get

        public static com.cyc.kb.Context get(CycObject monad,
                                     TimeInterval time)
                              throws com.cyc.kb.exception.KbTypeException,
                                     com.cyc.kb.exception.CreateException
        Return a Context based on monad, but temporally qualified to time. There is no corresponding findOrCreate method, because this does not require that the temporally-qualified Microtheory already exist in the Cyc KB. If a context returned by this method is used in an assertion, the temporally-qualified microtheory will be automatically reified. The monad part of this context must already exist in the KB.
        Parameters:
        monad - a monadic microtheory. If this monad has a time specification (i.e. it isn't really a monad), the time specification will be replaced in the resulting context.
        time - the temporal qualification for the * resulting Context.
        Returns:
        a new context
        Throws:
        com.cyc.kb.exception.KbTypeException
        com.cyc.kb.exception.CreateException

        Parameters:

      • findOrCreate

        public static ContextImpl findOrCreate(String nameOrId)
                                throws com.cyc.kb.exception.CreateException,
                                       com.cyc.kb.exception.KbTypeException
        Find or create a Context object named nameOrId. If no object exists in the KB with the name nameOrId, one will be created, and it will be asserted to be an instance of #$Microtheory. If there is already an object in the KB called nameOrId, and it is already a #$Microtheory, it will be returned. If it is not already a #$Microtheory, but can be made into one by addition of assertions to the KB, such assertions will be made, and the object will be returned. If the object in the KB cannot be turned into a #$Microtheory by adding assertions (i.e. some existing assertion prevents it from being a #$Microtheory), a KBTypeConflictExceptionwill be thrown.
        Specified by:
        findOrCreate in interface com.cyc.kb.Context
        Specified by:

        Specified by:

        Parameters:

        Returns:
        a new Context
        Throws:
        com.cyc.kb.exception.KbTypeException
        com.cyc.kb.exception.CreateException

public static ContextImpl findOrCreate(CycObject cycObject)
                                            throws com.cyc.kb.exception.CreateException,
                                                   com.cyc.kb.exception.KbTypeException
        Deprecated. 
        Find or create a Context object from cycObject. If cycObject is already a #$Microtheory, an appropriate Context object will be returned. If object is not already a #$Microtheory, but can be made into one by addition of assertions to the KB, such assertions will be made, and the relevant object will be returned. If cycObject cannot be turned into a #$Microtheory by adding assertions (i.e. some existing assertion prevents it from being a #$Microtheory, a KBTypeConflictExceptionwill be thrown.
        Parameters:

      • findOrCreate

        public static ContextImpl findOrCreate(String nameOrId,
                                       com.cyc.kb.KbCollection constraintCol)
                                throws com.cyc.kb.exception.CreateException,
                                       com.cyc.kb.exception.KbTypeException
        Find or create a Context object named nameOrId, and also make it an instance of constraintCol in the default context specified by KBAPIDefaultContext#forAssertion(). If no object exists in the KB with the name nameOrId, one will be created, and it will be asserted to be an instance of both #$Microtheory and constraintCol. If there is already an object in the KB called nameOrId, and it is already both a #$Microtheory and a constraintCol, it will be returned. If it is not already both a #$Microtheory and a constraintCol, but can be made so by addition of assertions to the KB, such assertions will be made, and the object will be returned. If the object in the KB cannot be turned into both a #$Microtheory and a constraintCol by adding assertions, a KBTypeConflictExceptionwill be thrown.
        Specified by:
        findOrCreate in interface com.cyc.kb.Context
        Specified by:

        Specified by:

        Parameters:

        constraintCol - the collection that this #$Microtheory will instantiate
        Returns:
        a new Context
        Throws:
